libfixposix
------------------------------------------
The purpose of libfixposix is to offer replacements for parts of POSIX whose
behaviour is inconsistent across *NIX flavours.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.6-1
  libfixposix-devel-0.5.1-1bl1
  libfixposix4-0.5.1-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.9.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.39-1
  cygport-0.35.4-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  libtool-2.4.7-1
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/sionescu/libfixposix

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/sionescu/libfixposix/archive/refs/tags/v0.5.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libfixposix-0.5.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libfixposix-0.5.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libfixposix-0.5.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfixposix-0.5.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfixposix4-0.5.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfixposix-devel-0.5.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libfixposix)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libfixposix.README
  /usr/share/doc/libfixposix/LICENCE
  /usr/share/doc/libfixposix/README.md

(libfixposix4)
  /usr/bin/cygfixposix-4.dll

